install [python extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemname=ms-python.python) - install [pylance extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemname=ms-python.vscode-pylance) - install [lsp-pyright](https://github.com/emacs-lsp/lsp-pyright) package ```elisp (use-package lsp-pyright :ensure t :hook (python-mode . where you have installed `boto3-stubs` type checking should now work. no explicit type annotations required, write your `boto3` code as usual. ### sublime text - install `boto3-stubs[redshift-serverless]` with services you use in your environment: ```bash python -m pip install 'boto3-stubs[redshift-serverless]' ``` - install [lsp-pyright](https://github.com/sublimelsp/lsp-pyright) package type checking should now work. no explicit type annotations required, write your `boto3` code as usual. ### other ides not tested, but get_value() -> associationtypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, types for `session.client` and `session.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in documentation_summary: The HTML text introduces `mypy-boto3-redshift-serverless` version 1.34.16, a Python package available on PyPI that provides type annotations for the `boto3.RedshiftServerless` service. These annotations are generated with `mypy-boto3-builder` version 7.23.1 and are compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright. The package aims to help developers find and fix potential bugs by enabling better code completion and type checking. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The package is maintained by Vlad Emelianov and supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.8 to 3.13. Instructions for installation, uninstallation, and usage across different IDEs and tools are provided, along with information on explicit type annotations, client annotations, paginators annotations, literals, and type definitions.
